Thought we explored this subject on Virus-l last year and the concept
was found to be a good one so long as the user was notified of what 
was happening and given the opportunity to decline (and be logged off).

I know of several antivirals that use this technique and have for some 
time.

I expect that the real question is one of sematics. There is a place for
controlled rules-based self-progagating code. There is no excuse for
code that propagates without control or that attempts to disguise the act
of propagation. From what I have seen of your vritings, what is being
called a virus is really a program that modifies other programs *designed
for that purpose*. 

Malicious software (what we call viruses) on the other hand, modify 
programs that were not intended to be modified, often disrupting 
systems as a result.

Like  was said, sematics, but not only are you using terms out of the 
